result.name: Pacific Coffee

reviews.text: I like Pacific coffee for spinach feeta cheese roll, potato salad, English tea latte, Caffe moca, cappuccino, cheese cake, brownie, matcha tea and all were good.... totally different and my favorite is Youghurt....One can try....and have pleasant English breakfast....
Good coffee shop located in the Wan Chai district.  Easy access for wheel chairs. Disabled toilets. Offers good coffee and small meals and snacks. Accepts cash. Octopus and credit cards.

There is buckets on tables because they have AC pouring issues.. Unfortunately it happened right on my Dell laptop with water literally starting flooding very strongly 5 cm from it. My iPhone got all wet and my laptop fortunately OK. They offered nothing for such disagreement, weither a free coffe or even an apologise from the manager. 

Quite dangerous actually because the water wasn't pouring directly from AC but through lighting appliance!

The toilets were out of service for more than one week now.

Oh and also, this is Pacific cofee so expect a troublesome mobil app, weak loyalty program and lack of healthy offerings.

I recommend going to the Starbucks next door, they know better what customer service means.
Somehow this branch’s coffee and service quality is lower than some others I have tried.

Long que in the morning... Why? Because its good😊. Especially for non locals.. A good variety of sandwiches yoghurt fresh juice and of course hot n cold coffees incl teas. Recommended all day for a brake..
